1
00:00:12,000 --> 00:00:14,625
[insects chirping]

2
00:00:21,333 --> 00:00:24,750
[in Burmese] Where did you get
the <i>mohinga?</i>

3
00:00:24,833 --> 00:00:28,417
They made it at the center,
so I asked for some.

4
00:00:31,625 --> 00:00:32,625
[slurps]

5
00:00:38,583 --> 00:00:43,833
The guy taking us home said
we'll have to wait a few more days.

6
00:00:45,833 --> 00:00:47,667
The police patrols are really strict,

7
00:00:47,750 --> 00:00:50,667
so he can only bring the boat in
at certain times.

8
00:00:52,083 --> 00:00:54,542
When I go out during the day,

9
00:00:55,875 --> 00:00:59,875
make sure you lock the door.

10
00:01:11,667 --> 00:01:13,042
It's a little salty, huh?

11
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:20,500
I miss Grandma's cooking.

12
00:01:25,167 --> 00:01:30,083
Hang in there. Just a little longer,
and we'll be back with Grandma.

13
00:01:36,583 --> 00:01:37,542
[bowl thuds]

14
00:01:38,208 --> 00:01:39,250
[utensils clatter]

15
00:01:40,458 --> 00:01:43,333
- [sobbing]
- [melancholic music playing]

16
00:01:50,958 --> 00:01:52,042
[sobs]

17
00:01:55,333 --> 00:01:57,458
[music darkens]

18
00:02:06,750 --> 00:02:10,208
THE EVIL LAWYER

19
00:02:10,292 --> 00:02:12,583
[music concludes]

20
00:02:12,667 --> 00:02:15,458
[footsteps approaching]

21
00:02:17,125 --> 00:02:20,208
DR. KORN SOPHONCHITRAK

22
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:22,792
[Pui] Hello, doctor.

23
00:02:25,125 --> 00:02:26,500
Hello.

24
00:02:35,583 --> 00:02:37,417
It's so bright in here.

25
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:41,542
Can I turn off the lights?

26
00:02:41,625 --> 00:02:43,917
[dreamy intriguing music playing]

27
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,833
I like it in the dark.

28
00:02:48,375 --> 00:02:49,583
Hmm…

29
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:53,958
How can I examine you
if the lights are off?

30
00:03:08,917 --> 00:03:11,250
Well, if you don't want to examine me yet,

31
00:03:12,875 --> 00:03:14,750
then I can examine you first.

32
00:03:14,833 --> 00:03:16,083
Don't.

33
00:03:16,167 --> 00:03:17,917
- [Pui smooches]
- [grunts]

34
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:19,208
[Pui moans]

35
00:03:19,875 --> 00:03:21,125
Doctor…

36
00:03:22,208 --> 00:03:23,875
- [Prangthip] Stop!
- [music stops]

37
00:03:25,042 --> 00:03:26,542
What kind of story are you making up?

38
00:03:26,625 --> 00:03:27,500
[echoing whoosh]

39
00:03:31,042 --> 00:03:33,667
Our defense in court
will be that it was consensual.

40
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:37,875
You're going to make everyone think
my husband willingly slept with her?

41
00:03:37,958 --> 00:03:40,625
Exactly. I told you
I didn't sleep with my patient.

42
00:03:41,542 --> 00:03:44,625
None of it is true… you know that.

43
00:03:45,875 --> 00:03:47,042
Find a different angle.

44
00:03:47,708 --> 00:03:50,333
Even if my husband sleeps around,
that's a private matter between us.

45
00:03:50,417 --> 00:03:52,792
But she has a transfer slip
for 50,000 baht from him,

46
00:03:52,875 --> 00:03:55,000
which practically proves
he slept with her.

47
00:03:55,083 --> 00:03:59,375
Just say she's blackmailing him.
My husband is just a gullible fool.

48
00:03:59,458 --> 00:04:00,708
That's not a crime.

49
00:04:02,167 --> 00:04:04,792
That's the plan.
If you can't do it, we're done.

50
00:04:06,292 --> 00:04:09,375
With evidence this clear,
even I'm telling you it's impossible.

51
00:04:09,458 --> 00:04:11,292
Do you think anyone else can do it?

52
00:04:16,125 --> 00:04:17,167
Want to find out?

53
00:04:17,250 --> 00:04:18,625
[soft tense music playing]

54
00:04:18,708 --> 00:04:21,250
[Prangthip]
Don't be so confident, Attorney Jittri.

55
00:04:21,333 --> 00:04:24,583
The only reason I hired you
is because my husband insisted.

56
00:04:25,833 --> 00:04:28,125
I have many other ways to end this.

57
00:04:29,375 --> 00:04:31,208
You're not the only way out of this.

58
00:04:37,750 --> 00:04:39,458
We can't say it was consensual.

59
00:04:39,542 --> 00:04:42,250
If word gets out
that I slept with a patient,

60
00:04:42,333 --> 00:04:43,250
my career is over.

61
00:04:43,333 --> 00:04:44,375
[Prangthip] Korn!

62
00:04:49,708 --> 00:04:50,708
[music fades]

63
00:04:50,792 --> 00:04:54,208
Damn! The doctor's wife
is fierce as hell.

64
00:04:54,708 --> 00:04:56,708
I thought she was a damn warden.

65
00:04:58,250 --> 00:04:59,542
So what's next, boss?

66
00:05:00,500 --> 00:05:02,875
Do we fight or fold?

67
00:05:04,125 --> 00:05:05,250
We can't back out now.

68
00:05:06,208 --> 00:05:08,625
We still need a doctor
to testify in Mek's case.

69
00:05:10,417 --> 00:05:13,875
Contact Tah's show.
We need to go big on this one.

70
00:05:13,958 --> 00:05:15,292
[Kung in English] Yes, sir!

71
00:05:15,375 --> 00:05:17,333
[in Thai] I won't miss a single detail.

72
00:05:19,125 --> 00:05:20,292
What is it now?

73
00:05:22,917 --> 00:05:23,917
Nothing.

74
00:05:25,208 --> 00:05:27,458
Have you found the Burmese woman
you're looking for?

75
00:05:28,750 --> 00:05:30,792
I found her brother,
but still no sign of her.

76
00:05:32,042 --> 00:05:34,583
I told you. You'll never find her.

77
00:05:36,792 --> 00:05:38,708
Why are you so sure I won't find her?

78
00:05:43,792 --> 00:05:47,042
Because I've never seen anyone
who disappeared come back.

79
00:05:47,125 --> 00:05:49,125
[dark pensive music playing]

80
00:05:49,208 --> 00:05:52,125
[woman]<i> Muleng, let go of me.</i>
<i>I have to go find Dad.</i>

81
00:05:52,208 --> 00:05:53,250
[girl]<i> Dad is dead!</i>

82
00:05:53,333 --> 00:05:56,125
Do you hear me? Dad is dead!

83
00:05:56,208 --> 00:05:57,500
- [fast thud]
- [sniffles]

84
00:05:57,583 --> 00:05:59,000
He's still alive!

85
00:06:03,958 --> 00:06:05,167
Muleng.

86
00:06:06,208 --> 00:06:07,375
Muleng.

87
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:11,750
Muleng.

88
00:06:12,792 --> 00:06:14,000
Muleng.

89
00:06:15,208 --> 00:06:16,708
Muleng!

90
00:06:17,458 --> 00:06:18,875
[music fades]

91
00:06:18,958 --> 00:06:20,667
[Tah muffled] Attorney Jittri.

92
00:06:20,750 --> 00:06:22,000
Attorney Jittri.

93
00:06:22,917 --> 00:06:25,167
- [clearly] Attorney Jittri.
- Yes?

94
00:06:25,250 --> 00:06:27,542
I can ask your client anything, right?

95
00:06:27,625 --> 00:06:28,583
Go for it.

96
00:06:28,667 --> 00:06:31,083
Okay, the audience is my witness.

97
00:06:31,167 --> 00:06:33,417
I'm doing my job. I can ask anything.

98
00:06:33,500 --> 00:06:35,500
They can't sue me later.

99
00:06:35,583 --> 00:06:37,208
So, let's begin.

100
00:06:37,792 --> 00:06:38,750
Dr. Korn.

101
00:06:38,833 --> 00:06:40,208
With all due respect,

102
00:06:40,292 --> 00:06:43,000
do you know what netizens
are calling you right now?

103
00:06:44,458 --> 00:06:45,667
They're calling you…

104
00:06:45,750 --> 00:06:47,583
Excuse my language, "the horny doctor."

105
00:06:48,292 --> 00:06:50,125
So I'm going to ask you right here.

106
00:06:50,208 --> 00:06:52,500
Let's talk man-to-man.

107
00:06:52,583 --> 00:06:55,417
Confirm in front of everyone now
that you didn't do it.

108
00:06:56,208 --> 00:06:57,875
I absolutely did not do it.

109
00:06:57,958 --> 00:07:00,042
I've been a doctor for over 20 years.

110
00:07:00,125 --> 00:07:02,208
I'd never throw my life away
over something like this.

111
00:07:02,292 --> 00:07:03,417
That's understandable.

112
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:07,292
But there's one point everyone questions,
and it really is suspicious.

113
00:07:07,375 --> 00:07:08,417
You transferred the money.

114
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:10,708
- [Korn] Mm-hmm.
- You can see why people would think

115
00:07:10,792 --> 00:07:13,125
it was hush money.
Why else would you transfer it?

116
00:07:13,875 --> 00:07:16,417
Well, when the patient came to see me,

117
00:07:16,500 --> 00:07:18,250
she said she had back pain.

118
00:07:18,333 --> 00:07:19,958
But based on my initial examination,

119
00:07:20,042 --> 00:07:23,292
I thought the actual cause
might be a uterine tumor,

120
00:07:23,375 --> 00:07:26,125
so I recommended
she get checked at the hospital.

121
00:07:26,208 --> 00:07:29,625
But she said she had no money,
so I helped her out.

122
00:07:29,708 --> 00:07:31,875
Do you know why many people
don't believe you?

123
00:07:31,958 --> 00:07:34,042
Because you transferred a lot of money.

124
00:07:34,125 --> 00:07:35,750
Isn't 50,000 a bit too much, doctor?

125
00:07:35,833 --> 00:07:37,250
[guest] Not too much at all!

126
00:07:37,833 --> 00:07:39,208
How is it too much?

127
00:07:39,292 --> 00:07:42,458
Whoa, calm down, ma'am.
It's not your turn yet.

128
00:07:42,542 --> 00:07:44,833
Camera, pan over here a bit.

129
00:07:44,917 --> 00:07:47,875
Please introduce yourselves, ladies.
These are Dr. Korn's fans.

130
00:07:47,958 --> 00:07:48,958
What are your names?

131
00:07:49,042 --> 00:07:50,833
- Kanchana.
- [Tah] Kanchana.

132
00:07:50,917 --> 00:07:51,875
Karuna.

133
00:07:51,958 --> 00:07:53,250
- [Tah] Karuna.
- Yes.

134
00:07:53,333 --> 00:07:55,167
Both are Dr. Korn's fans.

135
00:07:55,250 --> 00:07:56,958
- You're his patients.
- Yes.

136
00:07:57,042 --> 00:08:00,708
People in the area call him
Dr. Korn, The Angel's Touch.

137
00:08:00,792 --> 00:08:02,833
One touch and you're cured, like that.

138
00:08:02,917 --> 00:08:05,458
The doctor is highly skilled and kind.

139
00:08:05,542 --> 00:08:08,417
He's taken care of us
for over ten years, right?

140
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:10,750
And no one has ever complained about him.

141
00:08:10,833 --> 00:08:14,083
I think the person complaining,

142
00:08:14,958 --> 00:08:18,083
- she's a real bitch.
- Ah, let's not--

143
00:08:18,167 --> 00:08:19,667
No bad words, please.

144
00:08:19,750 --> 00:08:21,833
We have a lot of kids watching at home.

145
00:08:21,917 --> 00:08:26,167
I understand your frustration
since you both believe in Dr. Korn,

146
00:08:26,250 --> 00:08:27,833
but the person who should be angrier,

147
00:08:27,917 --> 00:08:30,167
or at least more upset
is probably this person.

148
00:08:30,250 --> 00:08:31,833
Camera, pan over a bit.

149
00:08:32,667 --> 00:08:33,917
This is…

150
00:08:34,000 --> 00:08:35,250
Excuse me.

151
00:08:35,333 --> 00:08:38,500
- Ms. Prangthip, Dr. Korn's wife, right?
- [Korn] Yes.

152
00:08:38,583 --> 00:08:41,500
[Tah] Being supportive like this means
things are cleared up at home, right?

153
00:08:41,583 --> 00:08:42,500
[Korn] All sorted out.

154
00:08:42,583 --> 00:08:45,375
- [soft intriguing music playing]
- [indistinct chatter]

155
00:08:45,458 --> 00:08:47,292
[Tah] Then let me ask you
another question.

156
00:08:47,375 --> 00:08:48,500
Why do you think…

157
00:08:48,583 --> 00:08:52,042
[Mek] On Facebook, people are supporting
the doctor and the victim equally.

158
00:08:52,125 --> 00:08:55,542
But on TikTok,
the doctor is totally trending.

159
00:08:56,083 --> 00:08:57,458
Why are we doing this to him?

160
00:08:57,542 --> 00:08:59,500
It's totally useless in court.

161
00:08:59,583 --> 00:09:01,208
[music fades]

162
00:09:01,292 --> 00:09:02,417
Don't you get it?

163
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:04,667
It's called public condemnation, idiot.

164
00:09:06,208 --> 00:09:07,167
Hmm.

165
00:09:07,250 --> 00:09:08,708
Judges are still human.

166
00:09:08,792 --> 00:09:10,458
They're bound to cave under pressure.

167
00:09:10,542 --> 00:09:11,792
[tutting]

168
00:09:11,875 --> 00:09:14,792
- [quirky music playing]
- [Tah speaking indistinctly]

169
00:09:14,875 --> 00:09:18,167
I better keep my voice down, too.
Need to keep my voice down.

170
00:09:18,958 --> 00:09:21,417
- [music concludes]
- If there are any remaining issues

171
00:09:21,500 --> 00:09:23,708
or if there's anything else to discuss,

172
00:09:23,792 --> 00:09:25,167
I'll see you in court.

173
00:09:25,250 --> 00:09:29,958
<i>Well, viewers, please use your discretion.</i>

174
00:09:30,042 --> 00:09:31,625
<i>Listen to all sides,</i>

175
00:09:31,708 --> 00:09:34,125
<i>and think about what incidents like this</i>

176
00:09:34,208 --> 00:09:36,500
<i>can teach us.</i>

177
00:09:36,583 --> 00:09:38,500
<i>Sometimes, to accuse someone,</i>

178
00:09:38,583 --> 00:09:41,583
<i>you need sufficient evidence. Otherwise--</i>

179
00:09:41,667 --> 00:09:43,167
[cell phone ringing]

180
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:44,250
[Pui sniffles]

181
00:09:44,333 --> 00:09:46,625
THE MOTHER POWER LAWYER

182
00:09:46,708 --> 00:09:49,167
[dark somber music playing]

183
00:09:50,250 --> 00:09:51,417
[Pui] Hello?

184
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:53,333
[lawyer speaking indistinctly over phone]

185
00:09:53,417 --> 00:09:54,583
I didn't watch it.

186
00:09:54,667 --> 00:09:57,250
I didn't watch it,
and I didn't read anything.

187
00:09:57,333 --> 00:10:00,125
[lawyer] <i>That's good.</i>
<i>And you deleted all the apps?</i>

188
00:10:00,208 --> 00:10:01,583
Yes, I deleted all the apps.

189
00:10:01,667 --> 00:10:04,583
I did everything you told me to do.

190
00:10:05,167 --> 00:10:06,458
[lawyer] <i>Good job.</i>

191
00:10:07,125 --> 00:10:10,042
<i>Don't worry about a thing.</i>
<i>We'll fight together.</i>

192
00:10:11,125 --> 00:10:13,500
I'm fully prepared for this.

193
00:10:14,042 --> 00:10:16,125
I'll fight with everything I've got.

194
00:10:16,208 --> 00:10:18,542
[lawyer]<i> Okay. I'll come by tomorrow.</i>

195
00:10:18,625 --> 00:10:20,375
<i>Let's rehearse one more time.</i>

196
00:10:20,458 --> 00:10:21,625
Yes.

197
00:10:21,708 --> 00:10:23,042
[music fades]

198
00:10:31,708 --> 00:10:35,500
[Pang] If we're talking about the East,
this place is in the top five.

199
00:10:35,583 --> 00:10:38,542
The owner is Chaiwut.
People call him Chai.

200
00:10:39,458 --> 00:10:41,125
He does it all.

201
00:10:41,208 --> 00:10:43,958
Cold storage, transport,
and fishing boats.

202
00:10:45,542 --> 00:10:47,875
When Seya and his sister
sneaked into Thailand,

203
00:10:47,958 --> 00:10:49,375
the broker brought them here.

204
00:10:49,458 --> 00:10:52,333
But Seya was separated
and sent to work on a boat.

205
00:10:52,417 --> 00:10:56,208
Scammed workers get their IDs taken away
and are forced to work off their debt.

206
00:10:56,292 --> 00:10:58,917
They could work themselves to death
and never pay it off.

207
00:11:00,167 --> 00:11:02,083
Every trip out to sea lasts years.

208
00:11:03,250 --> 00:11:05,792
Some die and never come back.

209
00:11:09,125 --> 00:11:11,333
If the three siblings used to work here,

210
00:11:12,542 --> 00:11:14,958
does that mean Anan is involved in this?

211
00:11:15,542 --> 00:11:19,417
Thai fisheries were banned by Europe
due to reports of human trafficking.

212
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:21,417
The government issued strict regulations.

213
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:24,375
The Fishery Association
did their best to clean things up.

214
00:11:25,208 --> 00:11:28,542
But Chai is the only one
still getting away with it.

215
00:11:29,875 --> 00:11:31,042
What do you think?

216
00:11:36,083 --> 00:11:40,792
[sentimental ballad
playing over cell phone]

217
00:11:41,917 --> 00:11:42,958
Hello?

218
00:11:45,542 --> 00:11:46,542
Seya.

219
00:11:47,458 --> 00:11:49,375
[in Burmese] Seya, calm down.

220
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:51,292
Speak slowly. What happened?

221
00:11:51,375 --> 00:11:53,458
[foreboding music playing]

222
00:11:57,333 --> 00:11:58,333
Seya.

223
00:11:59,542 --> 00:12:02,917
I don't know what to do anymore.

224
00:12:03,875 --> 00:12:07,000
- Where did they take my sister?
- Seya, calm down, okay?

225
00:12:07,083 --> 00:12:09,250
- What happened?
- Nay Oo is gone.

226
00:12:12,250 --> 00:12:14,083
[in Thai] Did you find Nay Oo?

227
00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:17,583
I lied.

228
00:12:19,167 --> 00:12:21,333
I brought Nay Oo to hide here.

229
00:12:22,125 --> 00:12:24,250
We were going to run away together.

230
00:12:24,333 --> 00:12:26,083
[sobs] But she disappeared.

231
00:12:31,583 --> 00:12:33,833
It has to be those cops, right?

232
00:12:34,750 --> 00:12:36,000
The ones that came for me.

233
00:12:36,083 --> 00:12:37,250
Calm down.

234
00:12:37,333 --> 00:12:39,125
She might have run away somewhere.

235
00:12:39,208 --> 00:12:40,625
No way.

236
00:12:42,292 --> 00:12:45,542
Our great-grandmother gave us these
when we crossed into Thailand.

237
00:12:46,458 --> 00:12:48,417
She wouldn't leave it behind like this.

238
00:12:51,792 --> 00:12:53,708
[sobbing softly]

239
00:12:54,375 --> 00:12:56,958
If they do something to Nay Oo too…

240
00:13:01,042 --> 00:13:02,167
I'll kill them.

241
00:13:02,250 --> 00:13:03,625
[Seya breathes shakily]

242
00:13:03,708 --> 00:13:05,833
Take it easy, Seya. Calm down.

243
00:13:07,500 --> 00:13:09,500
[music rises]

244
00:13:13,292 --> 00:13:15,042
[music fades]

245
00:13:15,125 --> 00:13:16,958
[Tah over video]
<i>This issue is still trending…</i>

246
00:13:17,042 --> 00:13:18,917
Holy shit. The tables have turned.

247
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:20,542
[Tah] <i>…about what really happened.</i>

248
00:13:20,625 --> 00:13:23,500
<i>Right now,</i>
<i>I'm sitting with Attorney Manao…</i>

249
00:13:23,583 --> 00:13:26,000
Damn, she looks spicy.

250
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:29,042
Mek.

251
00:13:29,583 --> 00:13:32,625
- Mek, look at this.
- Give me a sec.

252
00:13:32,708 --> 00:13:35,667
I'm telling you,
you need to see this right now.

253
00:13:36,375 --> 00:13:38,500
<i>Actually, I invited her</i>
<i>to come on the show today,</i>

254
00:13:38,583 --> 00:13:41,958
<i>- but she really isn't ready.</i>
- [Tah] <i>That's understandable.</i>

255
00:13:42,042 --> 00:13:44,542
Look, that's Manao,
the boss's old assistant.

256
00:13:44,625 --> 00:13:46,583
She's Pui's lawyer now.

257
00:13:46,667 --> 00:13:49,000
[Tah]<i> …in some angles…</i>

258
00:13:49,083 --> 00:13:51,792
Anyway, did you watch the last episode?

259
00:13:51,875 --> 00:13:52,750
[Manao] I did.

260
00:13:52,833 --> 00:13:55,333
Did you see that their side insisted

261
00:13:55,417 --> 00:13:58,208
that the doctor didn't do it
and that he's a very good person?

262
00:13:58,292 --> 00:14:00,208
Witnesses filled the whole studio.

263
00:14:00,292 --> 00:14:02,458
As for the 50,000-baht transfer,

264
00:14:02,542 --> 00:14:05,250
it was out of pity
and a genuine desire to help.

265
00:14:05,333 --> 00:14:08,042
They'll do whatever it takes
to make people believe them.

266
00:14:09,292 --> 00:14:11,958
I know exactly what kind of person
their lawyer is.

267
00:14:12,042 --> 00:14:14,917
Huh? You mean Attorney Jittri?

268
00:14:16,833 --> 00:14:20,292
Wow. [clicks tongue]
What does that smirk mean?

269
00:14:20,375 --> 00:14:24,125
Does it mean you believe
they're definitely not telling the truth?

270
00:14:25,167 --> 00:14:28,667
Well, I want everyone
to judge for themselves from this clip.

271
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:31,833
THE TABLES TURN! DOCTOR IN TROUBLE
THE MOTHER POWER LAWYER REVEALS EVIDENCE

272
00:14:31,917 --> 00:14:34,125
[Pui over video]
<i>I'll press charges against you</i>

273
00:14:34,208 --> 00:14:37,167
<i>for non-consensual sex.</i>

274
00:14:37,708 --> 00:14:38,625
[sniffles]

275
00:14:38,708 --> 00:14:42,208
- [Korn] <i>Listen, how much do you want?</i>
- [ominous music playing]

276
00:14:42,292 --> 00:14:44,958
<i>- Is 20,000 enough?</i>
- [Pui] <i>I don't want your money.</i>

277
00:14:45,042 --> 00:14:47,083
<i>I want justice.</i>

278
00:14:49,292 --> 00:14:52,917
[Korn]<i> Alright, fine.</i>
<i>I'll give you 50,000.</i>

279
00:14:53,500 --> 00:14:54,500
<i>But just once.</i>

280
00:14:54,583 --> 00:14:56,292
<i>Let's consider it a win-win.</i>

281
00:14:56,375 --> 00:14:59,125
Shit, caught red-handed on video.

282
00:14:59,750 --> 00:15:01,583
Dr. Korn is finished.

283
00:15:01,667 --> 00:15:04,542
- Case closed.
- Hold on.

284
00:15:04,625 --> 00:15:05,833
[Tah] <i>I have to ask you,</i>

285
00:15:05,917 --> 00:15:08,542
<i>aren't you afraid they might argue…</i>

286
00:15:08,625 --> 00:15:12,458
<i>They might say she intentionally</i>
<i>filmed this to blackmail the doctor.</i>

287
00:15:12,542 --> 00:15:15,917
<i>If she meant to blackmail,</i>
<i>wouldn't she have spent the money by now?</i>

288
00:15:16,542 --> 00:15:20,208
<i>Here's the evidence.</i>
<i>Dr. Korn transferred 50,000 baht.</i>

289
00:15:20,292 --> 00:15:24,042
<i>Transfer evidence.</i>
<i>A direct slip from Dr. Korn himself.</i>

290
00:15:24,125 --> 00:15:26,458
[Tah]<i> He transferred immediately</i>
<i>and even sent the slip?</i>

291
00:15:26,542 --> 00:15:30,875
[Manao]<i> Yes. As soon as she got the money,</i>
<i>she immediately filed a police report.</i>

292
00:15:30,958 --> 00:15:34,625
[Tah]<i> Well, let me ask. Do you have</i>
<i>any message to send to the other side?</i>

293
00:15:35,375 --> 00:15:38,292
[sighs] <i>I'll see you in court.</i>

294
00:15:38,958 --> 00:15:40,292
[music fades]

295
00:15:40,375 --> 00:15:42,000
[Kung] Manao's upgraded herself.

296
00:15:42,083 --> 00:15:44,417
Now she's as sour as her name.
A full package.

297
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:46,042
She's getting too good at this.

298
00:15:46,125 --> 00:15:48,125
She wasn't this good when she was with us.

299
00:15:48,208 --> 00:15:50,750
- [Pui] <i>I'll press charges against you…</i>
- [Kung] Ah, found some lime.

300
00:15:50,833 --> 00:15:53,333
<i>- …for non-consensual sex.</i>
- Lime, huh?

301
00:15:53,417 --> 00:15:56,500
Throw out all the lime juice
in the fridge, Nemo.

302
00:15:56,583 --> 00:15:58,083
- Hey.
- [Kung] Yeah?

303
00:15:58,167 --> 00:15:59,875
The wording in the clip is weird.

304
00:15:59,958 --> 00:16:01,208
What is it?

305
00:16:01,292 --> 00:16:03,542
"Charges against you
for non-consensual sex."

306
00:16:04,083 --> 00:16:05,625
It sounds like she memorized it.

307
00:16:05,708 --> 00:16:08,458
Well, maybe Pui knows the law.

308
00:16:08,542 --> 00:16:09,917
People can be educated, you know?

309
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:11,625
It's possible she knows the law,

310
00:16:11,708 --> 00:16:13,958
but what kind of person
speaks in legal jargon like that?

311
00:16:14,042 --> 00:16:17,083
And her tone sounds totally deliberate.

312
00:16:17,583 --> 00:16:21,125
Tricking the doctor to transfer the money
to use it for the police report.

313
00:16:25,500 --> 00:16:27,417
What if Attorney Manao

314
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:31,167
was the one who planned for the victim
to entrap Dr. Korn?

315
00:16:31,250 --> 00:16:34,250
- [Kung] Right.
- If the court finds out about this,

316
00:16:34,333 --> 00:16:36,042
this evidence will hold no weight.

317
00:16:37,042 --> 00:16:38,167
[foreboding music playing]

318
00:16:38,250 --> 00:16:39,333
Holy shit.

319
00:16:40,042 --> 00:16:41,792
I've seen the boss use this tactic.

320
00:16:42,792 --> 00:16:46,208
Manao worked here for a long time.
She learned some of Jittri's tactics.

321
00:16:47,583 --> 00:16:48,708
[sniffs, chuckles]

322
00:16:48,792 --> 00:16:50,583
You're pretty sharp, damn it.

323
00:16:50,667 --> 00:16:52,583
The problem is how we can prove it.

324
00:16:52,667 --> 00:16:55,375
[chuckles] Have you heard
of the Pantip Conan?

325
00:16:57,750 --> 00:17:00,750
[dark intriguing music playing]

326
00:17:04,375 --> 00:17:05,917
[Kung] The Mother Power Lawyer.

327
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,417
Manao used to lash out at me all the time.

328
00:17:12,375 --> 00:17:13,958
The clip was filmed on November 30th.

329
00:17:14,042 --> 00:17:16,500
That means Pui
had contacted Manao before that.

330
00:17:16,583 --> 00:17:18,042
- Nemo.
- Yes, sir.

331
00:17:18,125 --> 00:17:19,958
Facebook, IG, X, TikTok.

332
00:17:20,042 --> 00:17:21,875
Search back to November 30th.

333
00:17:21,958 --> 00:17:24,625
- Get on it.
- You got it, boss.

334
00:17:25,833 --> 00:17:27,583
THE MOTHER POWER LAWYER

335
00:17:27,667 --> 00:17:31,125
- [mouse wheel rattling]
- [intense intriguing music playing]

336
00:17:36,375 --> 00:17:39,833
PHYSICAL ABUSE BY A HUSBAND
IS A CRIMINAL OFFENSE

337
00:17:40,958 --> 00:17:44,000
Manao's IG is full of her baby pictures.
She's so obsessed.

338
00:17:44,708 --> 00:17:49,417
Oh, so cute and chubby! So adorable!

339
00:17:49,500 --> 00:17:52,500
What the hell is wrong with you?
Keep searching.

340
00:17:53,583 --> 00:17:57,333
Trying to be the honey
to her lime? Bastard.

341
00:18:01,208 --> 00:18:04,250
INTERNATIONAL DAY FOR THE ELIMINATION
OF VIOLENCE AGAINST WOMEN

342
00:18:08,792 --> 00:18:09,958
[music turns tense]

343
00:18:10,042 --> 00:18:13,458
I NEED ADVICE.
IF I SUSPECT A DOCTOR DID SOMETHING TO ME,

344
00:18:13,542 --> 00:18:15,042
BUT HAVE NO PROOF, WHAT SHOULD I DO?

345
00:18:15,125 --> 00:18:17,417
THE MOTHER POWER LAWYER:
CAN YOU GIVE ME MORE DETAILS?

346
00:18:17,542 --> 00:18:19,167
WHAT HAPPENED AND WHAT KIND OF DOCTOR?

347
00:18:19,250 --> 00:18:22,208
I HAD BACK PAIN,
SO I WENT TO AN ORTHOPEDIC CLINIC.

348
00:18:22,292 --> 00:18:25,375
BUT HE MADE ME TAKE OFF MY SHIRT
AND TOUCHED ME, CLAIMING IT WAS TREATMENT.

349
00:18:25,458 --> 00:18:28,000
THE MOTHER POWER LAWYER:
MAY I DM YOU?

350
00:18:28,625 --> 00:18:30,375
- [mouse clicks]
- [mouse wheel rattles]

351
00:18:45,792 --> 00:18:47,500
- Shit, I think I found it.
- [Kung] Huh?

352
00:18:48,108 --> 00:18:49,442
Where?

353
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:55,750
You think this is it?

354
00:18:56,875 --> 00:18:58,083
I think it is.

355
00:18:58,167 --> 00:18:59,458
The plot is way too familiar.

356
00:18:59,542 --> 00:19:02,708
Damn. Are you a psychic, Mek?

357
00:19:03,292 --> 00:19:05,125
You've got a damn sixth sense.

358
00:19:06,042 --> 00:19:09,583
Back the fuck off.
Keep your smelly breath away.

359
00:19:09,667 --> 00:19:10,792
Click on her profile.

360
00:19:10,875 --> 00:19:11,833
[mouse clicks]

361
00:19:14,042 --> 00:19:15,417
BLISSIS LOCKED HER PROFILE.

362
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:17,500
[Mek] All locked up. We can't snoop.

363
00:19:17,583 --> 00:19:19,792
- [chuckles]
- [music concludes]

364
00:19:20,792 --> 00:19:23,375
You know any top-tier internet sleuths?

365
00:19:23,958 --> 00:19:25,375
- [daring music playing]
- [Mek] Damn.

366
00:19:25,458 --> 00:19:27,792
[chuckles] That's not me.

367
00:19:31,417 --> 00:19:32,458
[music concludes]

368
00:19:32,542 --> 00:19:34,750
[Kung] What the hell are the glasses for?

369
00:19:34,833 --> 00:19:36,750
Blocking blue light, bro.

370
00:19:36,833 --> 00:19:40,125
[upbeat electronic music playing]

371
00:19:40,208 --> 00:19:42,333
[mouse clicking]

372
00:19:43,625 --> 00:19:47,039
[mouse clicking]

373
00:19:47,125 --> 00:19:49,250
[keyboard clacking]

374
00:19:53,250 --> 00:19:54,875
PLUS-SIZE WOMEN'S CLOTHING

375
00:19:54,958 --> 00:19:56,250
[mouse clicks]

376
00:19:56,875 --> 00:19:58,125
[mouse wheel rattles]

377
00:19:58,208 --> 00:20:00,417
[keyboard keys clacking]

378
00:20:04,167 --> 00:20:05,250
[keyboard keys clack]

379
00:20:05,333 --> 00:20:07,375
Wait. Look at this for a sec.

380
00:20:08,708 --> 00:20:10,417
This one. Click on this one.

381
00:20:12,333 --> 00:20:13,250
[music concludes]

382
00:20:13,333 --> 00:20:16,750
JUST A REMINDER I GOT THROUGH IT.
BYE, MY FRIEND, BIPOLAR.

383
00:20:16,833 --> 00:20:19,167
[Kung] Holy shit. Bipolar.

384
00:20:19,250 --> 00:20:21,750
[tense music playing]

385
00:20:25,292 --> 00:20:26,292
[mouse clicks]

386
00:20:26,375 --> 00:20:29,125
I CAN'T ESCAPE IT.
WELCOME BACK, MY OLD FRIEND.

387
00:20:29,208 --> 00:20:31,458
RISPERIDONE
PSYCHIATRIC MEDICATION

388
00:20:31,542 --> 00:20:32,708
[Kung] Seems pretty serious.

389
00:20:33,917 --> 00:20:36,008
Should we use this against her?

390
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,875
- Don't do that, man.
- [music fades]

391
00:20:40,958 --> 00:20:44,375
It has nothing to do with the case.
And don't tell this to Jittri.

392
00:20:44,458 --> 00:20:47,583
Hey, I can't do that.
The boss needs to know everything.

393
00:20:47,667 --> 00:20:48,750
It's too sensitive.

394
00:20:48,833 --> 00:20:51,708
Just Pui's posts
talking to Manao are enough.

395
00:20:51,792 --> 00:20:53,000
[bag zipper closes]

396
00:20:53,083 --> 00:20:54,042
Hey.

397
00:20:55,083 --> 00:20:57,292
Damn, you're as kind as Santa Claus.

398
00:20:57,792 --> 00:20:58,667
[Mek] I'm out.

399
00:21:01,583 --> 00:21:04,042
[Nemo] Damn, I wasted all that time
searching for nothing.

400
00:21:04,125 --> 00:21:05,542
No! Don't go out yet.

401
00:21:05,625 --> 00:21:06,792
[tense music playing]

402
00:21:06,875 --> 00:21:08,458
There's a random car parked out front.

403
00:21:08,542 --> 00:21:09,667
I don't know who sent them.

404
00:21:09,750 --> 00:21:11,208
- [Kung] Bro.
- [Nemo] Fuck, who is it?

405
00:21:11,292 --> 00:21:13,917
Mai is blocking them.
I don't know whose car it is.

406
00:21:15,583 --> 00:21:18,167
They've been here a while.
Just parked there, staking us out.

407
00:21:18,250 --> 00:21:19,750
I've got Ek's gang watching them.

408
00:21:19,833 --> 00:21:20,875
[Kung] Damn it.

409
00:21:20,958 --> 00:21:23,792
[Meuk] Headlights are on too.
If the battery dies, don't help them out.

410
00:21:23,875 --> 00:21:25,500
- [Kung] Idiots.
- [Nemo] What's the plan?

411
00:21:25,583 --> 00:21:26,750
I'll handle this.

412
00:21:27,250 --> 00:21:29,333
Hey, fuckers!

413
00:21:29,417 --> 00:21:30,750
[banging on car]

414
00:21:30,833 --> 00:21:32,875
- [Kung] Who the fuck are you?!
- [Meuk] Film them!

415
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:34,750
- [Kung] Damn it!
- What the fuck?

416
00:21:35,583 --> 00:21:36,833
- [Kung] Get out!
- Get out!

417
00:21:36,917 --> 00:21:39,000
You think I don't know, you bastard?!

418
00:21:39,083 --> 00:21:40,292
Get out!

419
00:21:40,375 --> 00:21:42,500
- [music stops abruptly]
- [insects chirping]

420
00:21:44,083 --> 00:21:45,083
[car door closes]

421
00:21:45,708 --> 00:21:46,792
Why are you here?

422
00:21:50,333 --> 00:21:51,375
Girlfriend?

423
00:21:53,833 --> 00:21:56,042
A relationship
I knew nothing about. [sniffs]

424
00:21:59,292 --> 00:22:00,917
I banged on her car for nothing.

425
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:03,167
Almost broke my hand, damn it!

426
00:22:04,250 --> 00:22:05,625
[Kung groans]

427
00:22:06,292 --> 00:22:07,500
Boss!

428
00:22:09,917 --> 00:22:12,042
[intriguing musical sting plays]

429
00:22:12,625 --> 00:22:14,667
Nay Oo did sneak over to see Seya.

430
00:22:15,208 --> 00:22:18,375
But the room I saw was completely trashed.

431
00:22:19,167 --> 00:22:21,333
There must have been a struggle.

432
00:22:21,417 --> 00:22:23,417
And there's no way
she ran away on her own

433
00:22:23,500 --> 00:22:26,167
because she promised Seya
they'd go back to Myanmar.

434
00:22:27,542 --> 00:22:30,292
Pang has her team spreading the word now.

435
00:22:31,125 --> 00:22:34,292
If there are any leads on Nay Oo,
they'll contact us right away.

436
00:22:40,250 --> 00:22:41,958
I should've believed you that day.

437
00:22:45,125 --> 00:22:46,125
I'm sorry.

438
00:22:51,292 --> 00:22:53,458
Do you have any information on
who took Nay Oo?

439
00:22:53,542 --> 00:22:55,250
[pensive music playing]

440
00:22:55,958 --> 00:22:57,042
[sighs deeply]

441
00:22:58,125 --> 00:23:00,250
There are no cameras around there.
Nothing at all.

442
00:23:00,333 --> 00:23:01,708
It's a workers' camp.

443
00:23:01,792 --> 00:23:03,833
Pang and I asked everyone,

444
00:23:03,917 --> 00:23:05,583
but nobody saw a thing.

445
00:23:07,417 --> 00:23:08,917
[breathes deeply]

446
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:10,542
What should we do next?

447
00:23:15,833 --> 00:23:18,208
Since we don't have any leads
on where Nay Oo went,

448
00:23:18,292 --> 00:23:20,667
I still have to keep working on
Dr. Korn's case.

449
00:23:23,875 --> 00:23:24,875
Mek.

450
00:23:26,458 --> 00:23:29,167
What if Nay Oo really was taken
by Anan's men?

451
00:23:31,417 --> 00:23:33,125
Do you think she's still alive?

452
00:23:45,708 --> 00:23:47,792
[music darkens]

453
00:23:51,333 --> 00:23:52,500
[music concludes]

454
00:23:52,583 --> 00:23:54,042
CRIMINAL COURT

455
00:23:54,125 --> 00:23:59,000
WITNESS HEARING: DR. KORN'S CASE

456
00:23:59,917 --> 00:24:03,167
- He's a great doctor.
- I just had my knee surgery.

457
00:24:03,250 --> 00:24:04,917
- I can walk fine now.
- [indistinct chatter]

458
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:08,625
- [Kung] What did you do? Play soccer?
- [Kanchana] Who would dare do that?

459
00:24:17,958 --> 00:24:20,958
[soft tense music playing]

460
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:37,667
[Manao] When did you find out
your daughter was violated?

461
00:24:37,750 --> 00:24:41,333
When she started having
chronic back pain last year,

462
00:24:41,417 --> 00:24:43,167
she began taking painkillers every day.

463
00:24:43,250 --> 00:24:44,125
[music concludes]

464
00:24:44,208 --> 00:24:46,625
But it got so bad
that they stopped helping,

465
00:24:46,708 --> 00:24:48,250
so we decided to go see a doctor.

466
00:24:48,333 --> 00:24:51,542
Dr. Korn, the defendant in this case.

467
00:24:52,667 --> 00:24:54,542
[Pui's mother] Yes. It was him.

468
00:24:57,083 --> 00:24:58,917
After we got back from the doctor,

469
00:24:59,667 --> 00:25:01,542
she started acting strangely.

470
00:25:02,542 --> 00:25:06,292
She kept to herself
and wouldn't leave her room.

471
00:25:07,500 --> 00:25:08,833
Until one day,

472
00:25:10,042 --> 00:25:12,667
I heard her crying quietly in her room.

473
00:25:13,625 --> 00:25:16,875
So I kept pressing her,
and she finally told me.

474
00:25:19,458 --> 00:25:20,833
Pui told me that…

475
00:25:22,250 --> 00:25:24,292
on the day she went to the clinic,

476
00:25:25,625 --> 00:25:29,625
the doctor said this kind of pain

477
00:25:29,708 --> 00:25:31,833
could be a uterine tumor.

478
00:25:33,583 --> 00:25:36,750
So he asked to do a pelvic exam.

479
00:25:38,042 --> 00:25:39,125
And then…

480
00:25:40,833 --> 00:25:43,833
he raped her.

481
00:25:43,917 --> 00:25:46,458
[dark, somber music playing]

482
00:25:48,167 --> 00:25:49,125
[exhales deeply]

483
00:25:50,208 --> 00:25:51,250
[inhales sharply]

484
00:25:51,958 --> 00:25:53,458
He told her that…

485
00:25:54,333 --> 00:25:55,667
he's a doctor.

486
00:25:57,125 --> 00:25:58,958
Everybody respects him.

487
00:26:01,333 --> 00:26:03,042
But people like us,

488
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:06,083
no one would believe a word we say.

489
00:26:06,167 --> 00:26:08,042
[Pui's mother breathes shakily]

490
00:26:11,083 --> 00:26:13,458
Your Honor, please help my daughter.

491
00:26:20,417 --> 00:26:21,875
[Manao] No further questions.

492
00:26:23,542 --> 00:26:25,625
Defense counsel, you may cross-examine.

493
00:26:27,833 --> 00:26:30,292
[music fades]

494
00:26:39,208 --> 00:26:40,583
Were you already aware…

495
